well montana did it again my heart is full rested and refreshed to jump back into normal life catching rainbow trout brown trout and carp with a fly rod on the bighorn river definitely doesnt suck so thankful i could experience my second trip to with a group of men working through their faith together
i already miss the beauty of gods creation in montana so he painted this for me as i land in nashville
i love watching a storm roll in and montana gave me a gorgeous show

and my latest project is finally complete an 8 farm table to replace the one i built 15 years ago the top on that one cupped and bowed as the seasons changed i was a total rookie woodworker back then and now im just barely above rookie status with much better tools and a few more skills of course as with every project id change a few things but im happy with it overall

20 years 7300 days 4 kids 2 states 10 homes 10 jobs countless dreams and 1 us happy 20th anniversary angela i married way above my head and im still blown away that i got you my dream girl youre my best friend the best mother in the world i could go on and on i love you meandyou

is this thing still on figured id come back to instagram to document our huge european vacation flew to boston this morning and had a nice day getting as much in as possible before our flight to london in a couple hours i always love my time in boston norm

amazing day in london with incredible weather feels like weve only seen a tiny bit of this great city even though weve walked 7 miles so far definitely need to come back for more were heading to venice tomorrow
venice was incredible now to the rental car place so we can drive into the alps
we were able to hit 4 of the 5 villages of cinque terre in one day theyre only accessible via boat train or by hiking from one to the next along a 22mile trail amazing
florence was really fun but definitely different than all of the other parts of italy weve seen so far tomorrow were heading to rome
im absolutely blown away by the history i saw today in rome from buildings that are 2000 years old to standing in the actual cell where paul was imprisoned wow wow wow
rome im pretty sure ill never again have the chance to see and to experience as much history in one single day as i did today im truly blown away and thankful
only half a day in copenhagen so far but dang i love this city i think we need to move here
incredible city definitely makes me want to come back to denmark and explore outside of copenhagen

day 2 in copenhagen and the final day of our epic family vacation flying home tomorrow to our normal life but more importantly to our elsie ive missed that little girl like crazy only cried once today because i forced myself to push through the final day without her but oh man i cant wait to get my hands on my baby

exactly one year ago today we flew international gcm yyz yow grand cayman is a major cruise ship port while we were at a museum in george town my husband remembers people coughing near us at the time we didnt know much about the virus that was quietly making its way around the world a week after we returned home our workplace doors closed for nonemergency access and we started working from home shortly after that i had a terrible cold for a month the health line nurse told me my symptoms did not match the requirements for covid testing and i probably just had a cold forever a mystery no antibodies test did i have it maybe not one thing i am sure of looking forward to the vaccine jabs this photo has nothing to do with that story these littles wait patiently for me to finish the day job hours my studio and office are the same place and i am surprisingly able to keep the two separate unfortunately my studio time hangs out on the back burner more than id like ill get to you guys someday

today was a day where the clay made me work for it some days youre just off and thats okay i havent thrown since early december and theres been a lot of loss and stress in our lives since then today was my day to finally scratch an itch to get back on the wheel to feel like me again a less empty me these stupid pots should never have been i should have quit not long after wrestling to center the first ball i tell my students if you arent centered then your clay wont be potting is as much a state of mind as it is technical skill my mind wasnt here yet each one of these pots shows an imperfection that flowed out from my center today and maybe thats exactly what i needed the crud had to come out and as it did i wrestled it and cursed it and lo and behold something was formed from all of that i guess sometimes we do need a good fight with ourselves throwingmylifeaway

im likely ahead of myself here but i dont care i want to go to this workshop i want to work my butt off for two weeks and learn as much as i can about wood firing and by doing anyone care to throw me 1500 plus airfare in exchange for some pottery and eternal gratitude repost with so the workshop i am teaching filled on the first day but i am teaching a very different one at my pottery in wisconsin this summer and i just opened registration today limited to 7 participants 6 places left june 30july 13 this is one of my favorite images from the workshop i taught at my pottery in gresham last summer the workshop is called the intimate anagama in the image sits alone with the hot kiln pouring over the kiln log his intensity is matched by the fire beside him his involvement is complete and we see him in this intimate moment the workshop is designed to create this kind of intense learning experience there is community work there is alone time there is equal part in decision making there are demos a guest artist community meals and you leave with 12 cubic feet of your own work fired by you if you are trying to get a grasp of wood firing this workshop is for you see more details on my website in my profile or message me and will be assisting

this is what the bottom of a mug looks like when its in the middle of being trimmed excess clay is shaved away to do several things balance the weight of the mug reveal a level foot ring for the cup to sit on and a place for the glaze to stop and generally enhance the profile of the mug as a whole while this task is somewhat hypnotic and relaxing id much rather improve my throwing so that i can skip this step all together and not have a fatbottomed mug i love the process but at a certain point if you want to make any money at this craft you have to find ways to make your production more efficient goals potteriastudio clay pottersofinstagram claytrimmings turningclay turning stoneware maker mugshot giffingrip

another piece from a recent rakufiring coincidentally enough i didnt use raku clay which i understand can be risky because the that clay body is better suited to handle the thermal shock of plucking the pot out of an 1800 degree fire and throwing it a bucket of combustible material for 10 minutes and then submerging it in cold water to immediately cool it off a harsh process not made for the faint clay bodies this was highwater clays littleloafers a throw away demo pot to show my students how to use a hump mold it is covered with one glaze color red luster the areas that are green are where it has been oxidized and the shiny coppery red areas on the bottom are evidence of reduction in those spots i have a little bit of carbon to scrub off it still but even so its a super lustrous piece and no longer a throw away pot

some get a gold watch but for my early retirement i got this sweet name tag from the great people i worked with for the last 25 years im humbled and honored to be remembered by this name i already miss being a part of that team but am so thankful they helped me learn that theres greater value in how you do the work than what you do as a digital designer its my job to make things look good and work good on screen but the minute you put pixels over people your design fails putting each other first cultivated a family a level of respect an appreciation for diverse thinking and a commitment to fun i believe what grew out of that was better work and more successful design than if we had stuck to our strengths and been highly driven professionals this was work worth doing

the dd gaming table is done this was made for my buddy mike and the idea was to have a biiiiiig table that would fit 6 players and a dm comfortably but still fold away for storage when not in use it features individual slidein trays for each players personal stuff and plenty of space on the main tabletop for maps etc the legs fold up into the main body the trays store underneath the tabletop and the two halves collapse and latch together for storage the main body was made of birch and birch plywood while the legs are made of solid red oak everything is stained dark walnut with about 4 coats of semigloss lacquer finish to provide protection and some spillproofing this is by far the largest thing ive built to date and i learned a ton while doing it woodworking woodworkingproject yaywood woodwork woodworker woodworkersofinstagram igwoodworkingcommunity custommade customtable dnd dndtable dungeonsanddragons tabletopgames birch redoak craft crafted handmade madeinnj madeinnewjersey customfurniture walnutstain

i resisted for a long time but finally picked up a road bike once the covid shutdown started ive been doing longer rides to make up for my lost bike commutes i also began riding more on roads due to the trails being overcrowded that led to looking for something that was more comfortable on lengthier outings and easier on the climbs up the hills of arlington by the time i landed on a bike i wanted there were only two left in the country in my size due to everybody buying bikes this summer i contacted a shop in ohio that was willing to ship the bike to my local bike store and even cover the shipping and assembly costs still going to keep the trusty hybrid around for riding with the kids and commuting once i go back in to the office next year newbikeday roubaix lycra cycling biking specializedroubaix2020 sharetheroad nplusone

new year and a new office setup experimenting with a single display i realised the issues i had working on multiple displays i had i also found out what the limitations of one display to avoid decided to go with two 4k displays running at native resolution both lg27uk600 because an extra 250 for usbc option didnt see worth it mounted on a dual monitor arm so far having used this for about 2 weeks onoff its been the best lots more pixels to output on less physical space having it as two displays rather than a single ultrawide or super ultrawide means splitting work in a way that reflects my workflow few things to change still as well as some out of shot features i added that i may talk about in the future but yeah enjoying my new home office setup

blue november 01 im neil and if you didnt know im a type 1 diabetic this means my body doesnt produce insulin and i have to administer it myself using a hypodermic needle i have to calculate carbohydrates and insulin ratios to make sure my blood sugars stay at an even level every day over the month of november ill be going over different aspects of my life with diabetes and how the pandemic situation has changed things for me this will not a perfect account of how to live with diabetes but my life with type 1 diabetes any questions or like to know more about something please ask and ill try the best i can to provide a response bluenovember bluenovember bluenovemberproject type1diabetes diabetic t1d t1dlookslikeme t1d insulin insulindependent diabeticsofinstagram diabetestype1 diabetesuk diabeticlife novarapid diabeticwarrior morethanhighsandlows

blue november 05 blood sugars arent only affected by food and exercise but also emotions stress is an issue at the moment as were trying to get some flooring laid throughout our downstairs the issue being is the fitters are being difficult to the point they flat out refused to work so have to source some new fitters is causing a lot of stress for over a week now i can deal with stress when im in control but issues outside my control get to me and my blood sugars go up and down drastically suppose having a life that has a lot of planning and preparedness means that i expect it from others its quite an idea situation that everybody is on the same wavelength as you so ive come up with my own coping mechanisms that ill share in the future really helps with stress though bluenovember bluenovember diabeticlife stress stressedout mentalhealth mentalhealthmatters diabeticmentalhealth t1d type1diabetes type1diabetic type1diabeticproblems morethanhighsandlows

blue november 06 i often get asked about alcohol and how it affects my diabetes and the short answer it that is depends i have found that whisky is the best for me as it doesnt affect my sugars in any real way that limits me beers are interesting as some will drop my sugars and others will increase them and that varies not just type but brand as well its a little bit of a guessing game at times but you can sometimes quickly tell how its going to go just from how your lips react bluenovember bluenovember diabetes type1diabetes insulin alchohol beer larger whisky whiskey bloodsugars diabeticdrinking gin rum tequila t1d drink drinkstagram diabetic type1diabetic

blue november 07 today americans have made their choice on their next president elect to be biden and harris as vicepresident elect without getting too political this affects peoples diabetes in the states as their medication isnt free and their choice in leader will have a meaningful impact trump previously said hes getting insulin so cheap its like water but for a number of people its far from it many america diabetics die from lack of access i often see in american groups diabetics or their care givers asking how gangrene their foot can go before they need to do something about it common one is how to engineer vials to get that scrap of insulin out of it things we dont ever think about in the uk as we have the nhs but i do hope for america that biden and harris will expand the affordable care act making insulin more accessible for all bluenovember bluenovember diabetes diabetic insulin affordableinsulin type1diabetes diabetesawareness diabetesawarenessmonth t1dawareness t1d

blue november 08 heres the two hypodermics i rely on everyday the orange one is a rapid acting insulin that works along side eating a meal so i do that 3 times a day the lilac looking one is a long acting insulin and does a background dose for the day keeping everything even the way these work means i can be very flexible in my life within reason when i was younger i used to only do insulin twice a day but that meant strict food times plus that was a old school syringe and vial which ive not seen for a long time now bluenovember bluenovember hypodermic insulin needle syringe type1diabetic type1diabetes diabetesawareness diabetesawarenessmonth type1diabetesawareness insulindependent novorapid glargine lantus sanofi novonordisk

blue november 10 i spoke a little about the freestyle libre already this month but its been a massive change to my treatment its worth sharing more this is the little device on my arm a filament under the taking reading on my blood sugars the bit you see i believe acts as the storage and rfid device so i can tap my phone against it and get a reading its waterproof shower proof and can take a fair old knocking found this out when i was in italy last year ill keep one of these on for around 2 weeks then swap to the next one bluenovember diabetesawareness diabetesawarenessmonth diabetes diabetestype1 libre freestylelibre type1diabetes type1diabeteslookslikeme diabeticlife flashtesting digitalmedicine t1dlookslikeme t1d t1dawareness

blue november 11 so today is my nans birthday she died last year and its been strange as well as sad not having her around but ive many fond memories of her and a lot of my vivid ones where her with my diabetes stories of her learning to inject me using an orange then doing injections like she was throwing a dart blood tests where always feet in a bowl of warm water and then using my toes to get then blood if my sugars where high she make me run up and down the stairs genuinely she made it seem like having diabetes was fun despite growing older i knew how much it pained her to do things that are inherently painful to me but she never showed that side she made it an everyday thing bluenovember

blue november 12 ive said before i get bouts of anxiety and that really affects my blood sugars sometimes these are justified and others they come out of the blue and can make you feel awful to combat these waves i find being hyper focused on something takes that away and my go to is playing skilledhard games or games with a lot of story im focused on the story and the challenge thinking moves ahead whilst understanding whats going on my brain is doing a lot of work and almost resets itself and forgets about the anxiety its amazing that thanks to tech like the libre i can see the results of being anxious to that refocused that it does really help seeing sugars spiking and dropping then when playing a game theres this calm that causes my blood sugars to stabilise bluenovember mentalhealth diabetesawareness diabetesawarenessmonth anxiety anxietyrelief diabetesmentalhealth mentalwellbeing type1diabetic

blue november 13 i spoke about alcohol previously but i like to show that diabetes and drinking sessions can work if you are sensible nothing wrong with getting a buzz of an evening as you can have stable blood sugars ive just finished a whisky tasting session and blood sugars are doing good i have gotten proper drunk in the past and its affected me afterwards not a hang over as i dont get them but worse and have had alcohol poisoning that wasnt to my own fault that really scared those close to me but taking the proper course of action and youll be okay diabeteswise just everybloodything else bluenovember diabetesawareness diabetesawarenessmonth drinking diabetesalcohol type1diabetes t1d whisky

blue november 14 okay original plan for today didnt happen due to house stuff and low blood sugars but here i raise a glass to sir frederick grant banting who codiscovered insulin without his discovery my life and those with diabetes could be very different today is his birthday so why not raise a glass of crown royal in his honour bluenovember worlddiabetesday raiseaglass insulin diabetes

blue november 15 lets talk covid19 and diabetes see diabetics are in the extremely clinically vulnerable shielding group but were still heightened as a clinical group there have been a higher number of deaths of those with diabetes over the age of 40 than without our covid age is somewhat increased this is due to how our bodies cope when we get unwell as well find ourselves insulin resistant meaning that well need to tighten control of blood sugars and possible increase the amount of insulin well need to do whilst blood sugars are high we are more prone to complications and this starts a extremely uphill battle we have specialist sick day rules to follow that help control blood sugars and get us on the mend but as covid19 is still new and not much is known its advice is the best we can go on without knowing much else a number of diabetes groups are heavily researching the effects of the virus on diabetics to help reduce the risks and provide the best advice they can offer its still best advice to stay away and keep wearing the mask if im honest i like wearing a mask got an outlaw feel to it bluenovember diabetes covid covid19 diabetescovid diabetescovid19 diabetesawarenessmonth diabetesawareness type1diabetic

blue november 16 a news article today from the bbc spoke about diabetes burnout and how diabetics suffer from issues like depression and anxiety but also eating disorders whilst ive never been in the latter camp the first two i know well your life is a constant act of working out what you need to do to stay normal its constantly preempting the day do i need to take insulin should i bring my night when will i eat will i be able to get enough carb will i have too much carb should i even eat that you need to make a number of judgment calls in a day that can effect thing drastically you are forever assessing yourself and then judging when you make the wrong actions you dont ever pat yourself on the back as a good day is being a normal person theres a reason why diabetics need to be regularly screen for mental health issues as a day can be a massive mind fuck and that day can carry on for weeks or months you can hit a wall and say nah cant be bothered and then you really start to go downhill this is why i try to be a easy going solutions focus person theres enough stress to worry about so i rather not add to it bluenovember diabetes diabetesawarenessmonth metalhealth depression anxiety eatingdisorder mentalcare diabetesburnout burnout

blue november 18 freestyle libre sensor change over day every two weeks i go through this process and today i have the luxury of kerrie helping me do the process four photos today so ill explain 1 removing the old sensor you can see the adhesive residue on my arm and the hole where the filament goes under my skin 2 this is the applicator and yes that a huge fuck off needle in there to make things go in ill be honest it rarely hurts you do feel it but thats a good thing as you know its done its job 3 lining up the location for the location for the sensor luckily my arms are either defined or loose bluish average which helps find a good flattish location 4 and job is done another two weeks of readings ready to go bluenovember diabetes librechangeday libre freestylelibre cgm bloodglucose insulindependent type1diabetic digitalmedicine digitaltreatment

blue november 21 jelly babies these things are a life saver fact its often thought that diabetics should never eat sweets or anything with sugar but thats not true we just need to be careful and mindful of our eating habits thats goes for anything really but when we have low blood sugars and go into a hypo 46 jelly babies can literally save our life they are coated in sugar made with a lot of sugar and have hardly any fat that means that our body will start processing them really quickly and help bring our sugar levels up to normal range so sugar can be very good for you damn same we still have to pay vat on these things in the uk bluenovember type1diabetic hypotreatment jellybabies jellybabiessavelives hypo lowbloodsugar t1d t1dawareness

blue november 22 heres my kitchen floor why have i taken this picture it was five years ago today i had a seizure on this very floor that made me realise that i had to take my diabetes so much more seriously than did it was a waking hypo so i was groggy any way but kerrie spotted it and went down stairs to get my jelly babies and stuff for some reason i followed her down and into the kitchen thats when i dropped to the floor and started fitting not that i remember any of this but seeing the worry it put on so many peoples faces after the fact changed my perspective im lucky that the worse thing out of it was i lost my driving license for a year and everybody else had to drive me places but thanks to that experience im probably physically healthier despite the extra responsibilities i have to put on my self now take a mental toll its manageable bluenovember diabetes diabetic seizure seizuressuck diabeticseizure

blue november 23 one of the key things you can do as a diabetic is carb counting the idea is you can work out how much insulin you need to do based on how much carb you have where you can count it as not all carb is equal i find working out sums in my head a pain so i did what i know best and made a carb calculator app a carbulator if you will food that shows you carbs per serving are great but you may need to accurately add multiple then you get the ones that tell you per 100g and then it gets tricky for me so this does both and gives you an accurate whole number to work out your insulin dosage with little things making life a little easier bluenovember diabetes diabetesapp carbcounting carbohydrates react mobileapp mobiledevelopment reactmobile pwa digitalmedicine reactjs

blue november 24 how do you feel about a bit of maths every time you eat this is the sort of calculations a diabetic will have to work out to keep their blood sugars in check and know how much insulin to give themselves it a lot to process when you just want to chow down some diabetics will have their meals planned out and precalculated for the day so they are ready to eat knowing the insulin dosage they need but thats only half if you need extra insulin due to high sugars you need to work that out this only works out the carbs in food nothing else so if you do more or less activity in a day then that throws all that out hell some days your body doesnt want to play ball and those figures dont even fly bluenovember diabetes math mathmatics calculations bolus type1diabetes type1diabetesawareness food4thought mealplanning

blue november 25 feet are an important thing or things rather and we often dont think about foot care that much for a diabetic its one of the main problem areas we can have all those nerve endings can be damaged due to excessive blood sugars and cause things such as nerve damage leading to insensitivity to gangrene that would mean amputation its one of the most common issues ive seen diabetics have is their feet and more extreme issues too i tried to look my feet sanssocks of course and see if theres anything unusual including if there are any sharp objects in them and the loss of sensitivity can be so bad you dont know they are there bluenovember type1diabetes diabeticfootcare t1d highbloodsugar highbloodsugarproblems

blue november 26 eyes are another point of issue with diabetics again with the blood vessels and high blood sugars the eye can become easily damaged with most diabetics over 10 years developing some form of retinopathy its where the blood vessels start to break down and bleed out i have background retinopathy but this is to be expected and is nothing to worry about if i leave my eyes unchecked or ignore high blood sugars over a period of time my eye sight can start to be affected and eventually blindness this is one of the more worrying things for me for a number of reasons having yearly checks helps combat against any future possibilities as it can take a while to get to that serious stage bluenovember eyesight diabeticretinopathy bloodvessels blindness diabetesawareness healthcheck vision diabetescare

blue november 27 sometimes the issue with diabetes can immediately scare you and freak you out suffering a really horrible low paranoia waking nightmare and complete sense of unease very rarely this happens but when it does its a horrific mix that you cant escape and hope that eating food will help break you out of the cycle its literarily a waking nightmare that you can escape from so bad ive hardly touched my whisky tonight bluenovember

blue november 28 well after last night hypo okay again now this is how quickly things can turn around one moment you are sitting down fine the next your freaking out with extreme paranoia living an actual waking nightmare and massively unsettling constant dejavu but today im a lot better and even went out and got a christmas and carried it home so im more than okay now but now im more with it i can try to explain it better your body is aware and awake but your brain is struggling to work its confusing thoughts in your head with whats in the real world but with the normalcy of my anxiety being high ten in hypo everything starts to go wrong youre seeing things that arent there youre feelings are completely foreign you are not your own person but an observer in a body you want far from it took a while for me to come back around and even then i was still dipping in and out of that state all i could think outside some pretty horrific thoughts is why is this happening the recovery is never quick and its a delicate balance of getting something quick acting and something long acting to keep you up buts theres a super delicate balance with that its easier to not worry about going high and just eat loads loads of jelly babies and then and some thing fibrous its not easy when it goes wrong but luckily i had people around me to keep my head in the right place hate to be by myself when that happens as the worst could very easily happen bluenovember hypo wakingnightmare lowbloodsugar diabetes diabetic christmastree diabetesawareness nightlow

blue november 29 after having that rather long low followed by night hypo i thought i should treat myself to running a little higher than normal want to treat myself so been enjoying having some seasonal goodies in the form of lebkuchen cookies being diabetic doesnt mean you cant have there things just in moderation which people should be doing any way plus the great thing about moderation is the impact having something like this on the taste buds is more intense screw diets of not eating or strictly limiting by choice we all need positive things in life and if thats a sweet treat then make it so just dont go overboard bluenovember lebkuchen treatyourself diabetic type1diabetic hypo bloodsugars cookies

blue november 30 my last post on blue november and its after a day of nothing exciting diabeteswise which is a really good thing so ill finish off with selfie showing that diabetes looks like me its not a fat person nor skinny person young or old person just a average person that happens to have type 1 diabetes i didnt do anything to get it and probably wont know why i even got diabetes in the first place there are ideas but nothing established as fact everyday can be something different and scary it can also be a boring day diabetes is a daybyday treatment but as much as its apart of me as we like to say i am more than my highs and lows this is why i spend a month doing this to show a side i dont often publicly tsk about because this is my normal life that im very content with so to me it seems pretty boring but i massively appreciate the fact that so many people find this interesting and informative i really hope everybody who has followed this month has learned a little something and thats all i ask is you come away from these a little more informed so thanks to everybody for the messages likes and comments as always any questions on type 1 diabetes please feel free to ask me no matter how you feel about the question again thank you all also apologies for bad grammar and spelling im not good phone tapping words bluebovember diabeteslookslikeme morethanhighsandlows type1diabetic type1diabetes diabetic insulindependent

that time of the week where i pick a dram and tell you what i think and probably do an awful job explaining flavours its whisky wednesday todays dram from is a deanston 14yearold organic single malt 463 abv not knowingly tried an organic so thats something different here but its a highland whisky which is normally an easy drinker nothing offensive but enough to let you know youre drinking a whisky on the nose with this one it took me a while but it initially had a somewhat earthy aroma but didnt seem right a few more sniffs it struck me as a mix of fresh cooking apples and sweet malt the taste clears it brings out that sweet baking flavours of pears and muscovado a very warming sensation i often say that this sort fo profile in a whisky is after dinner one a desert whisky but that doesnt fit here an autumn whisky for sure with the finish having a medium length spice to it i think this is one for a fireworks night or halloween a whisky to watch the leaves change colour a nice understated whisky that wouldnt go amiss in a collection if youre reading this far down may i suggest you follow were doing monthly tastings via zoom and this week were sampling so something a little different follow or join and see about coming song to one of our friendly sessions whiskywednesday drinkstagram drinksbythedram deanston highlandsinglemalt highlandsinglemaltscotchwhisky scotch scotchwhisky singlemalt organic dram dramstagram autumnvibes autumnwhisky whiskylover whiskygram whiskyclub whiskytasting whiskysample

wow a busy week so far hence no uploads as of yet but tonight is whisky wednesday and so i must face that horrible task of opening a dram of something and sampling its liquid insides tonight is my last dram of xmas collection and its 15yearold single malt at 46 abv now the nose i immediately get that distinct raisin smell with that caramel or butterscotch hint and possibly apple or pears right at the end there the colour of this whisky might be skewing my views as well look at how deep that oaky brown is almost the same shade as my table the taste is very interesting nothing i was expecting its almost bitter like dark chocolate or even akin to a chocolate sauce youll pour over venison but the raisin flavours are super strong in this one reminds me of the red box raisins eating them as a kid there are spices flowing in there around the woody notes the finish is short with this one with more of the aromas staying around rather than the flavours itself this is an odd mix in a good way of an allnighter but also a savour whisky probably more of the allnighter one as i could easily be drinking this one around friends having a gas it makes me want to try more of the glenallachie range now as its a very distinct scotch that id love to keep in for folks to try whiskywednesday singlemalt glenallachie glenallachiedistillery whisky scotch scotchwhisky whiskylover whiskygram whiskysample drinksbythedram dram singlemaltscotch singlemaltscotchwhisky speyside speysidewhisky

its wednesday and i have a whisky as is the tradition i shall obnoxiously taste it and provide my level headed feedback that is more akin to somebody who is drunk and is trying to sound like they know what the hell they are talking about today is a dram of bunnahabhain 12yearold single malt 463 abv from they sent out their bimonthly bottle this week which is rather nice i must say and provided this sample with it ive tried a few rarer bunnahabhains plus their stiireadair which ive posted about previously and their range is quite complex whilst not massively into their stiireadair ive heard great things about this whisky normally with a whisky from islay you are expecting peat but doesnt typically follow suit which is no different here the nose immediately brings up spiced sundried fruits with a sweeter floral sense towards the end there reminds me of a strong alcohol wine at the end the taste is rich with nuts and fruit trail mix wise with that almonds apple cashews and citrus peel with a little toffee in there somewhere that finish is quick but fragrant with a little dryness to it almost coats the mouth no peat in this for me or even smoke so if you arent into that then you are very safe with this bottle i can see why summerton sent this sample with their main bottle i like it ive been looking at buying this for a while now but wasnt sure and ended up getting something else but i think ill need to have one of these in as a keeper its got a lot going for it at a reasonable price tag around 40 for a 70cl well worth a try whiskywednesday islay islaywhisky singlemalt singlemaltwhisky singlemaltscotch singlemaltscotchwhisky bunnahabhain bunnahabhainwhisky bunnahabhain12 scotch whiskylover whiskygram whiskytasting whiskyporn whiskey whiskeygram whiskeylover summertonwhiskyshots

hi im neil and im a type 1 diabetic i stab myself with insulin and draw blood those who followed me last year may remember i did a month of photos relating to my diabetes im doing it again this month and hope to teach even more to people about diabetes though ill mostly cover type 1 diabetes i hope to give facts about type 2 as well im also aiming to squash misconceptions and myths about this condition that many have but if you have any questions ill answer them no matter how personal no holds bar type1 type1diabetic type1diabetes t1d diabetic diabetes bluenovember diabetesawareness diabetesawarenessmonth bluenovember

for years as a kid i never knew that the bottom drawer of a fridge was a salad crisper its always been where ive kept my insulin the same goes for the butter shelf in the fridge thats where i keep my current insulin even the fridge at work the butter shelf houses my insulin type1 type1diabetic type1diabetes t1d diabetic diabetes bluenovember diabetesawareness diabetesawarenessmonth bluenovember

heres what i stab myself with four times a day its weird to think that the little droplet the insulin is what keeps me alive also this is the only way i can get my body to process it is via a needle its not as bad as it seems theres worse needles and this isnt the painful part of diabetes theres two parts that actually are but this little synthetic hormone this is my very life line type1 type1diabetic type1diabetes t1d diabetic diabetes bluenovember diabetesawareness diabetesawarenessmonth bluenovember insulin needle

this is a typical saturday night drink for me a glass of whiskey not normally this much but im getting rid of a bottle any way i like a drink and this is fine for my diabetes the main thing i need to be aware of is alcohol can lower blood sugars this can be a bit of a concern when going out for a session as i need to weigh up the sugar content of a drink against the alcohol what works for me is high alcohol as most of the sugar is gone so all i need to is top up on carbs what has happened due to this also is my tolerance is rather high so if im acting a bit drunk the more logical issue is im low its a way of enjoying yourself and feeling the nicer affects of alcohol without the worries of high blood sugars or confusion of drunk or low im not a fan of getting drunk either way i drink for flavour hence my enjoyment of rather expensive whiskies type1 type1diabetic type1diabetes t1d diabetic diabetes bluenovember diabetesawareness diabetesawarenessmonth bluenovember alcohol whiskey whisky whiskygeek

over the last few days my blood sugars have been a bit haywire can be a struggle to get it right either too high or too low you want to be fully compos mentis but at the same time you want to comfortable unfortunately its easier to stay high as a safety net type1 type1diabetic type1diabetes t1d diabetic diabetes bluenovember diabetesawareness diabetesawarenessmonth bluenovember

back to work today after a very emotional few days and my blood sugars has been awful drinking coffee doesnt help my sugars are dipping and spiking looking like a diagram for a load of black runs taking in carbs seem like theyre doing what it should then i get jittery till i crash luckily working from home i can get my self to a point where i can focus and carry on working with perseverance i managed to get my tasks done for the day its a mix of patience i enjoy what i do for a living and not letting the diabetes get the better of me type1 type1diabetic type1diabetes t1d diabetic diabetes bluenovember diabetesawareness diabetesawarenessmonth bluenovember

the ongoing fun of unruly blood sugars continues my go to pick up is jelly babies four of these and my sugars are back to normal then i all need is something fibrous to keep the levels up i over a longer period interestingly it needs to be done in order high sugar first then fibre otherwise the fibre blocks the sugar till its processed which can take a while also this was a bloody difficult photo to take as my hands were shaking so much type1 type1diabetic type1diabetes t1d diabetic diabetes bluenovember diabetesawareness diabetesawarenessmonth bluenovember

one of the biggest issues i have with diabetes is not the blood tests or injections or the really crap feelings i have nope its the fact that im limited in what i can drink the amount of soft drinks with sugarscarbs in them is the worst even if they say sugar free or zero sugar they could have carbs more often than not nowadays you may see me drink mainly pepsi max as thats what i know is safe and the only thing that tastes good for me fruit juices flavoured waters and also health drinks are shockingly bad for me weirdly this is mainly an issue in the uk in places like ireland and canada i can often pick a whole range of drinks to have with a true 00 carb content seems like a minor thing and it is but when your out and want a quick drink of something other than water youre massively limited if the uk truly wants to stop kids drinking sugary drinks then maybe do more to incentivise getting true sugar free drinks in the market last thing a lot of what you read about artificial sweeteners is bull type1 type1diabetic type1diabetes t1d diabetic diabetes bluenovember diabetesawareness diabetesawarenessmonth bluenovember

i love lazing at home playing video games im somewhat healthy i try and go to the gym when i can and i eat fairly healthy not diet healthy which 90 of it is bull some may see my video game lifestyle as s possible reason why im diabetic many people think diabetes is directly related to being overweight this is not true for type 1 or type 2 closest thing true to that is being overweight may increase likelihood of type 2 diabetes but its not a deciding factor in fact most people with type 2 arent overweight and most overweight dont develop it i think thats source from diabetes uk but i can fact check if anybody queries that with regards to my diabetes type 1 its most likely caused by genetics and unknown factors anybody can develop it at any time but type 1 is most likely to occur at development stages in life so if somebody has diabetes youll be mostly wrong to assume its their lifestyle actually i found out recently theres a whole host of body building groups that are made up of type 1 and 2 diabetics so healthy people can be diabetic type1 type1diabetic type1diabetes t1d diabetic diabetes bluenovember diabetesawareness diabetesawarenessmonth bluenovember

ive always struggled to explain what high blood sugars actually feels like theres different levels to it at first you just feel heavy under your skin you then get that feeling of lactic acid but more like of you were to tense your muscles really hard edging to the point of causing a cramp but constant then comes the sharp headaches when youre really high they almost paralyse you ive been taken to the floor before in sheer pain i thought i was having a brain aneurism but it was moving all over under my skin my pain levels are very high but the times thats happened its horrific type1 type1diabetic type1diabetes t1d diabetic diabetes bluenovember diabetesawareness diabetesawarenessmonth bluenovember

meet our wine director andy miller from venice ca i was touring playing music for a living in the past and would always look for new local craft beer to try from that it quickly turned into finding new wines natural wine wasnt a thing i was aware of at the time until a few of my older friends caught onto this little bar in los feliz bar covell it was the first time i had wine with varietals i was familiar with done in a totally different style the wines were fresh and bright acid driven and slightly funky a few restaurants and cocktail bars later i began working at a natural wine bar where my mind was blown by everything we carried grower producer champagne old skincontact wine from georgia hybrid grapes from the northeast and everything beyond id love to pour you something special and chat natty wine next time youre in

3 glasses of whiskey in feeling things if there is one thing this pandemic has reinforced for me it is patience patience to wait for things to come for the universe to provide this is a story about being patient i probably heard my first frank turner song about 8 years ago he was just starting to get airplay in the us he headlined kegs eggs in 2013 but i missed it i was finally finding my feet in denver healing after the collapse of a long term relationship i was dating someone new for the first time things were going well we were making plans like buying tickets to s fall tour that year but somewhere along the way that relationship fell apart differing love languages a fear of commitment and so i found myself with 2 tickets but no one to go with as the summer progressed someone new entered my life i knew it was a bad idea there were issues from the start those little red flags you ignore but before i knew it i was dating that new person and one of the first real dates we had was the ft show i had tickets for that night was about as perfect a night as i have ever had i fell in love that night with both the girl and the music one burned bright before exploding breaking my heart which in the end was ok because i had made it through most of my life without my heart truly being broken and at the time thats exactly what i needed the other love endured fts music has gotten me through every high low since that night at the show i was so caught up in all of it that i missed buying a poster for the tour for 7 years off on ive been trying to buy that poster had never even seen one for sale until a few weeks ago when i was idly perusing ebay while stuck back home in tn and there it was priced low enough to win after a short bidding war and now its mine ifs really just a piece of paper with an artists design on it but to me its a connection to that night that moment with someone new that feeling of falling in love and knowing there is nothing you can do to stop it i havent felt that since but i have patience

several months ago at the start of the pandemic i bought a turntable figuring vinyl would be a good habit to get into while stuck at home of course once it was delivered i needed a place to put it so i started shopping for standsconsolesvinyl storage inspired by and dumpster find turned record console quarantine project i went on the hunt on craigslist and found this art deco nightstand that looked to be the right size and fit a lucky break it took a while to assemble the necessary tools stain supplies etc and to research how to strip the paint and refinish it since id never done that before the end result is honestly better than i was ever hoping for i eyeballed the space where the two bottom drawers were when i bought the thing and wasnt actually sure vinyl would fit but it does perfectly sawed right through the crossbar and made a perfect cube my dad was always a handy person who did most house projects himself as an architect he designed and built the second story addition of the house i grew up in id scare my mom by climbing the scaffolding and hanging out on the roof with him while he worked he never let me get near the circular saw but i was always allowed to help mix concrete i havent often had much reason or need to do that type of stuff on my own as an adult but it feels really good to take an idea visualize the result gather the necessary tools and knowledge and execute the vision into something youre proud of highly recommended its made for a very fun weekend project and a nice addition to the room now i just need my backordered speakers to arriveupdate found the speakers on sale for a similar price at another retailer arriving friday yay swipe right for progress shots vinyl turntable artdeco quarantineproject

it took several months but the day finally arrived today and the universe reiterated once again that this press was meant to be mine once i arrived at the depot everything came together convinced the driver to turn around from another delivery to come right away before the folks at the crane company across the street left for the day the crane folks werent even supposed to still be there as they had sold the property to a developer and had planned to be moved out by the 1st within about 30 minutes they had a forklift over and my press down the ramp and at the door only hiccup was not having a pallet jack at the ready currently on loan to a board member luckily they were able to grab one of those too and now the press is where she will stay for a bit meet gertrude shes gonna rest at the depot for a bit while i am back home in tn for the winter but come spring i think we are gonna get on just great

12 or so years ago a young friendly and slightly obnoxious grey and white tuxedo cat showed up on our porch in tn not long after i had come home from a failed attempt at living and working overseas he had a pink collar and was very affectionate and happy and most importantly night after night he just stayed on the porch he would curl up on this rocking chair no bigger than the gourd sitting there now he caused a ruckus too by killing and gutting a couple of mourning doves much to my moms horror but then weve always had cats so having kills brought to us has never been surprising except the live snakes whoo boy since he wouldnt leave we began to feed him my mom had already taken in two stray cats but eventually she said we could bring him in and she would pay to take him to the vet and get checked out we did our due diligence and called shelters and checked if he was chipped but it was the start of the recession and lots of animals were abandoned his previous owners were gone and so he came into the house made friends with the other two cats and was given the name brutus because he brute forced his way into our home i was still dealing with the loss of a previous cat who died under the worst circumstances falling out a window in vienna and suffering for a week as vets tried their best to save him but it was clear that brutus was not going to take no for an answer and my mom made it clear that when i moved back to colorado he would have to go with me and so he did i was really worried about moving him back with me to tn i bought a fancy carrier and a thundershirt and calming spray the first part of the trip was pretty rough but we made it and in the end i realized that home for him wasnt the apartment we shared in denver home has always been wherever i am he is the most affectionate cat i have ever owned hes my buddy my best friend and i desperately wish he could live forever at least right now we are here and working through this rough patch together this is for both of us our ancestral home where it all began and where the next phase begins love you brutus

goodbye kiwi you were not mine but you were my favorite you were a houseguest through many lonely thanksgivings an exuberant greeter whenever i came over a lover of walks and the outdoors and completely devoted to your humans the minute your leash was reached for you lost all control of your excitement and it was glorious you had a wiggly butt that just would not quit you always exhibited the utmost control when waiting for permission to eat even though it was so so hard for you you wanted desperately to be friends with brutus but learned quickly to give him space when a guest at our place you forgot this lesson one time and it nearly cost you an eye eventually he let you sleep a mere foot away from him on the couch he tolerated you which is high praise from a cat you cheerfully accompanied me all the way up a 14er once though you were not enthused once we got to the summit you enjoyed meeting the bighorn sheep we were both very thirsty by the time we got down you lived a full life and had two companions that loved you deeply and many more who admired you and cared for you you were the cutest dog in the world with the most expressive eyebrow muscles imaginable the faces you would pull brought smiles to everyone i am so very sad you are gone but i am so happy for the time i got to spend with you and the trust your humans placed in me in letting me dogsit you over the years i am so sorry and for your loss you gave her a wonderful life and home she was the bestest doggo the world is less bright right now without her in it i will miss her dearly

today is a sad terrible no good day opened 7 years ago and gave soccer fans in denver a big enough space for all of us to congregate and support our teams its the place along with the bully where we ran bus shuttles to rapids games first with bulldog supporters group and later with stout street bulldogs its where i learned how hard it is to help manage and run an sg on a shoestring budget how to manage people who helped out to keep things going and how to keep friends even when we disagreed its where we drank to the success of the usmnt with bob ley alexi lalas where the american outlaws built their support during the world cup in 2014 and during every qualifiergold cupcopa america centenario where we celebrated after the snow classico because yes we really were at that game in a gorilla suit no less most importantly its where i fell in love with crystal palace and forged friendships that will last a lifetime those satsun mornings even at 5am with are a highlight of my week where i get to hang out with great friends and suffer the heartachejoy much more of the first of supporting our weird underdog working class south london team i love our odd collection of expatsrandos who all felt the same passion that drew us to palace i know we will find a new home and make it our own but i will desperately miss what we had here the relationships and friends and bonds weve made will survive i am heartbroken for the staff who got up at insane early hours or worked super late so that we could drink and laugh and hang out in a place with like minded fans you guys worked hard and sometimes got overwhelmed but your efforts were noticed and appreciated to john forget whos vision of a central soccer pub for all of denver became reality thank you for dreaming it and building it and bringing us all together i wouldnt have the life or friends i have without the three lions i will miss it immensely

london you beautiful mad wonderful city ive seen more of you this trip than ever before from rolling hills and fields in muddy commons to back alleys covered in wall to wall street art the diversity of experiences and people are like no where else in the world ive been none of this should work many might say it barely does but day after day of riding the trains and the underground and seeing people go about their day proves otherwise somehow through centuries and logistics and technology and good will it just does there was sun and rain top level and nonleague football and amazing art both on the street and in the galleries great food both on the go and when sat in a pub and always good friendship and conversation i couldnt have made this trip without the hospitality of jade and especially her mom who gave me a place to stay and home cooked meals and most importantly fresh coffee every morning im lucky to have such a good friend and shes lucky to have such a great family theres only one word that comes to mind whenever i visit london and this trip has been no different fantastic travel london

beauty is a choice i think we sometimes forget that our society incentivizes us to judge constantly to always see the negative to tear down anyone or anything that dares to rise above the fray but its still our choice to participate to comment or tweet or be rude to someone just because we can its so easy to resort to ugliness this fall has been the worst weather i think ive ever experienced in colorado snowstorms came early and havent stopped coming the last one was the biggest in 25 years tonight it snowed yet again not for long but long enough to really drive home how shitty its been we havent even hit december and it already feels like weve had more snow than entire years previous to this its disheartening its hard to get around the city its hard to even want to leave the warmth of home tonight i was determined to go out anyway to see good friends and to imbibe good drinks and to have good conversations that probably wont change the world but at least might make both participants think just a little bit deeper than before sure we commiserated about the weather hard not to its easy to complain but on the way home i chose to walk a few extra blocks out of my way to the park nearby to take this picture with the snow covered field in the foreground and the skyline of the city i love standing against the horizon it was easy to stop in the cold with wet snow creeping into my shoes and choose to see the beauty of this moment on a cold snowy night just the beauty of the snow and the lights of the city against the dark sky these moments are always there all around us we just have to stop and choose to see them to choose them over the ugliness beauty is a choice

it has been a decade if you are reading this weve survived thats something some of my friends havent when i look back its a bit daunting to consider how much has changed the whole decade feels like two halves at the end of 2009 i had finally managed to move to denver but it was on the back of a pretty major failure at a jobcareer i thought id be really good at id also just taken my mom on an amazing trip of a lifetime to vienna but even that was bittersweet as it was also the beginning of the end of the relationship that had brought me back there in the early part of this decade i had to start over from scratch and thats what i did i struggled but found work i went out and made new lifelong friends i even fell into new relationships which while they didnt last taught me the importance of communication listening how to have your heart broken and more importantly how to mend it and how to be comfortable being alone the first half of the decade i was filled with hope for the future of the world and our country but pretty down on my own life and future everything flipped in the latter half while im increasingly pessimistic about the world and the rise of everything awful in the last four years ive been much luckier in my personal life ive grown as a person ive traveled to places id only dreamed of i made new lifelong friends i found communities of creative likeminded people that i cant wait to engage with more in the new decade ive never been more excited or terrified of what comes next i have a rough plan execution will be in the details ive become more flexible more calm more focused and sometimes i almost feel ready for the challenges ahead heres to 2020 being the start of an amazing decade for all of us full of love and challenges and successes and failures and bouncebacks and survival happy new year

logistics have been easy the emotional side has not been since before this quarantine started i have been worried about pretty much only one thing my mom who is in the high risk category for the virus isolated at home in tn sometime earlier this week my mom fell this is a regular occurrence only this time she was unable to get back up normally meals on wheels would stop by and she would receive help but they only come once a week now on fridays it took me two days to realize something was wrong after multiple unanswered messages we called in a wellness check and the police found her on the floor near the front door shes in the hospital now and seemingly ok but shes going to be there for at least a week and after that she has to go to a long term care facility for rehab this means that the nightmare ive been having from the start of all this has suddenly become significantly more likely the two places i wanted to make sure she avoided are now the two places she has to be to recover from her fall the virus has been spreading mercilessly through nursing homes and other facilities if my mom catches it there is very little chance of her surviving i am scared i really really hope i get to see my mom again i hate that i cant go visit cant support her basically have to just sit here and worry which i know doesnt help on friday i went down to castlewood canyon state park i needed not just to go somewhere new and be in nature but i needed someplace calming and serene to help cope with all the uncertainty hanging out with 55 million year old rocks helped for a bit time seems to be passing really damn slowly right now i know all of us are going through a lot the daily onslaught of news and the amount of uncertainty about the future can be completely overwhelming im sharing what im going through because i think its important to share and ask for help when you need it no one should have to go through any of this alone
today it got too hot glad tomorrow should be cooler masks in the summer are gonna suuuuuck

tbt to this monday when i spent 8 wonderful hours at this park that morning i got off to a slow start and pretty early on i just became overwhelmed with sadness not over anything in particular maybe over everything my mom this pandemic the way people treat each other the horribleness and brutality that continues to be inflicted on black and marginalized people the lack of social connection the selfishness privilege entitlement and greed seemingly always on display the sheer stupidity of our leaders it was a lot and it was clear i was going to have to sit with that sadness for a bit but that didnt mean i had to stay home i made my way out to the park with no real plan just some water and a snack a cursory glance at the map at the trailhead was enough to set off the falls seemed like a reachable destination and turnaround point staunton is a beautiful place easy to hike and with lots of gentle elevation change for a decent workout i made it to the falls in about two hours and hung out there for a bit watching climbers rappel down the rockface by 515pm i decided i could push on to the overlook which put me high above the falls for a completely different perspective from there i discovered a shortcut back to the pond my final good decision was refusing to take the same trail back to the parking lot instead veering off on a longer trail that looped up to another dazzling view and then past an old mill friends i had over an hour on that trail of complete solitude and it was joyous not another living soul nearby hard to explain how much i needed that given our solitary current lifestyle but for an hour i didnt have to think about anyone not wearing a mask or being an asshole or anything as no one passed me on the trail by 720pm i had made it to the mill and challenged the sun to a race to see who would arrive first me back at the parking lot or the sun at its destination on the horizon the sun won but it was close the last gift nature had to give me was a fox that loped straight across my path at the parking lot seeking out a dinner of scraps beneath the picnic tables and i realized i was no longer sad

a few pics of animal friends i met at staunton state park on memorial day also a gnarly gothic looking stump not pictured a dazzlingly blue little bird that flew away before i could capture a zoomed in and slightly blurry pic

i made this 6 years ago it was an extra lockup i had a bit of time to make in a letterpress workshop i was taking over a weekend taught by at the time the ferguson protests were still raging and i was heartbroken seeing st louis a city i had called home for 5 years devolve into chaos i was heartbroken over michael brown a black man i did not know losing his life unnecessarily i was heartbroken at the comments and media coverage all bent on justifying a murder i spent every night following the coverage on social media arguing with people who didnt understand trying to get through to friends who werent ready to trying to find my voice and my place to speak out while also reconciling my privilege and status in this corrupt system weve built i learned i listened i expanded my exposure to black and marginalized voices and i sat with the pain and suffering they voiced i empathized as much as i could i took action too i joined the marches and protests here i took the print above and fashioned it into a protest sign i lay on the street and played dead to block traffic and in the end nothing changed here we are 6 years later and if anything its gotten worse some days i fear the only option is to run an immense privilege but i also see so much good being shared now mutual aid groups organizing outspoken activists and best of all this shared sense that this time maybe everyone i know gets it im not arguing with friends now the people i know are using their voices sharing resources boosting marginalized voices trying to help however they can we are not perfect and we all still have to reckon with our privilege and comfort and the gravitational pull of that its so much easier to sit behind a screen and be safe especially during a pandemic i hope we all challenge ourselves to do more to be willing to hit the streets to risk the tear gas and rubber bullets because the thing about equality is it really does affect all of us were all being held back by these backwards views we cant play it safe anymore our whole country is at risk lets not choose the warmth of the fire as it burns down around us

im not sure i should have quit my day job two weeks ago i returned home from visiting family in canada theyd given me a check for inheritance my aunt had left me on the ferry ride back to the states i talked with my girlfriend and we both decided i should put in my two weeks at my day job the store id been at for the last nine years take a portion of the money and try to draw comics full time take six months to dedicate to comics see what happens id been thinking of leaving that job for years but id been dreaming of doing comics full time all my life when i left for canada three weeks ago i had no concrete plans to quit yet yesterday was my last day at that job im thrilled overwhelmed and frightened about what ive done guess i better go make comics

crossposted from matthewbogartnet several months ago novelist comedian poet storyteller and president of write bloody publishing wrote me with a plan a friend of his was redesigning a huge building in a small town and wanted to turn it into a collection of shops designed by different creators he wanted derrick to dream big and design a bookstore derrick told me his plan for fascination station it was to be a train station with a checkout counter modeled after grand central stations information kiosk it would have cubby holes for reading set into in the back wall designed like bunks on a train car large displays would be inset in arches showing landscapes rolling by travel posters advertising departure times for famous fictional destinations would hang on one wall and shelves would roll away so folding chairs could pull out from a secret compartment and an audience could watch authors read from the back of a full size caboose as if they were on a whistlestop tour it sounded wonderful and derrick wanted me to draw it while i make detailed 3d models for my comics id never designed something like this something that was to become an actual physical place something that needed to fit in exact dimensions and be usable by flesh and blood people it was a heck of a lot of fun and the illustration came together in no time fascination station book store overhead view an overhead view of fascination station a write bloody bookstore sadly things fell through the fascination station only exists in these drawings but gosh does it make me want to go to a bookstore so i think i will

for the last 6 months weve been renovating a historic home in downtown grapevine tx it is not for the faint of heart we were finally able to move in last week and are going through the slow process of getting things like mirrors curtains and towel racks hung i didnt do a great job of posting pictures throughout but will try and catch up with a few after the fact this great room used to be 4 separate rooms with a pantry and water heater closet right in the middle most of the floors throughout the house are original 2 red oak from 1954 which we sanded and refinished with an almost clear stain that just had a small amount of white mixed in they turned out fantastic the kitchen is completely brand new with an 8 island added in for good measure what you dont see here is that the window next to the kitchen is soon to be replaced with another door and steps down to the back patio and pool area grapevinetx midcenturymodern historichome

yes this is a picture of a bathroom and yes im kind of fond of the floor i wanted to put some fancy type in the floor with wash your hands or you look nice today but the decision maker in the house wasnt having any of it prior to the remodel this bathroom didnt exist there was a third toilet in the house but it was oddly located in the laundry room one can only assume that folding laundry while using the facilities is a little known proper timemanagement technique noted for this one we did a matte finish 1 hexagon tile in black and white you might notice a couple pieces of tape on the floor though where were going to change out the colors due to our ocdness and the pattern being a little off come and visit and ill let you use this little gem of a halfbath i wont even charge you for it historichome midcenturymodern grapevinetx

repost with tss meidn lhettiln jaakon fiilikset kevn ensimmisen 10km matkan jlkeen helsinki10ll pari viikkoa takaperin greeting from our ambassador from his first 10k event this spring preparing for the helsinki half marathon helsinki 10 i havent raced a 10 k in years so i was a feeling a bit anxious on the race day thankfully the weather was warm maybe even a bit too warm and the course was really familiar to me after a light warmup i lined up with the 5730 pacers and was ready for the race the sun was shining and i was feeling quite thirsty on the starting line i figured that it was just the nerves and didnt think much of it at that time the race started and i managed to keep a good even pace of 540 545 minkm for the first 5 km at the start of 6 km my lower back started to ache and it affected by breathing rhythm luckily i was able to stretch my back while running and was able to continue but at the same time it meant that i slowed down to around 6 minkm pace for the kilometers 7 to 9 i picked up the pace on the final kilometer and crossed the finish line in 5846 for the upcoming races i have to take a closer look at my fluid intake to make minimize the possibility of cramps or aches along the way all in all helsinki 10 was a well organized race with a fast route ill be on the starting line next year thats for sure jaakko werunhelsinki hhm2019 helsinkihalfmarathon helsinkihalfmarathon ambassador lhettils
